### What happened?

On the page https://docs.trychroma.com/cloud/schema/schema-basics?lang=typescript

The package name is incorrect, also the `model` property to the constructor should be `modelName`.

contains: 

```typescript
import { Schema, VectorIndexConfig } from 'chromadb';
import { OpenAIEmbeddingFunction } from 'chromadb';

const schema = new Schema();

// Configure vector index with custom embedding function
const embeddingFunction = new OpenAIEmbeddingFunction({
  apiKey: "your-api-key",
  model: "text-embedding-3-small"
});

schema.createIndex(new VectorIndexConfig({
  space: "cosine",
  embeddingFunction: embeddingFunction
}));

// @snippet:example
// TODO: Add TypeScript example code here
const example = "hello";
// @end


```

should be:

```typescript
import { Schema, VectorIndexConfig } from 'chromadb';
import { OpenAIEmbeddingFunction } from '@chroma-core/openai';

const schema = new Schema();

// Configure vector index with custom embedding function
const embeddingFunction = new OpenAIEmbeddingFunction({
  apiKey: "your-api-key",
  modelName: "text-embedding-3-small"
});

schema.createIndex(new VectorIndexConfig({
  space: "cosine",
  embeddingFunction: embeddingFunction
}));

// @snippet:example
